==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phantom circuit
<hw>Phantom circuit</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The equivalent of an
additional circuit or wire, in reality not existing, obtained by certain
arrangements of real circuits, as in some multiplex telegraph
systems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phantomatic</ent>⟦br⟧
